Brown Sugar Pudding

INGREDIENTS

1 cup light brown sugar
3/4 cup milk
1 cup flour
1 teaspoon baking powder
1 teaspoon butter
1 cup pecans
1 teaspoon vanilla
1 cup brown sugar
1-1/2 cups hot water

INSTRUCTIONS

Mix together  1 cup brown sugar, milk, flour, baking powder, butter, pecans and vanilla and pour into 2-quart baking dish. 

In separate bowl mix together: 1 cup brown sugar and 1-Â½ cups hot water. Pour over first mixture. 

Bake in 375 F degree oven for 30 to 45 minutes. 

Serve and enjoy while still warm.
